\begin_layout Standard
Law of large numbers.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{n}=\frac{1}{n}\sum_{i=1}^{n}X_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{var}\left(Z_{n}\right)=\frac{\sum\sigma_{i}^{2}}{n^{2}}.$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P\left(\left|Z_{n}\right|>\epsilon\right)\leq\frac{E\left[Z^{2}\right]}{\epsilon^{2}}=\frac{\sum\sigma_{i}^{2}}{n^{2}\epsilon^{2}}.
\]

\end_inset

As 
\begin_inset Formula $n\to\infty$
\end_inset

, the probability 
\begin_inset Formula $P\left(\left|Z_{n}\right|>\epsilon\right)\to0$
\end_inset

.
